				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Tarn Macklin<a name="65661"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 5 04 12:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The Tarn Macklin encounter is bugged.  Tarn is supposed to spawn when you kill the Excavator with 6 guards.  When I went to pay him a visit, on each of the 6 spawn points were 5 mobs.  It looks like each time the Excavator is spawned 6 more guards spawn (even if the previous ones have not been killed).
<br />

<br />
My advice to anyone doing this is go check to see if Tarn Macklin is up before triggering him (you need to go through the wall / room in the centre of the zone before you can track him).
<br />

<br />
I also found that Tarn (like all his guards) can be Highsuned.  My first tactic was to pull all 31 of them to the other side of the wall and highsun Tarn back to his spawn point to be killed.  This worked but my friend did not have a healer and had to evac.  I was still kiting all the guards so faded when I got summoned by Tarn.  The guards had problems pathing back to their building effectivly leaving Tarn single and I pulled him (whilst invis) to the zone to kill (healer had just arrived)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><br>
Julan<br>
The Rathe</span></td>
