				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Tarn Macklin<a name="66489"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 10:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The easy way to pull and kill Tarn Macklin with one group.
<br />

<br />
When he spawns, he will be in a small open room with 3 Mercenary guards out front and 3 excavators behind him in the room.  If you tag him with bellow or HOS, he will run out with all 6 of his friends.  You can pull to any angle away from the house and fade will simply not split them apart.  Yes, all 6 of his friends are mezzable but the 3 mercenary guards out front are not lullable nor are they root/snarable and they are too high level to charm, even with Banshee.  So, how to you EASILY split this down to manageable one-group chunks?
<br />

<br />
Step 1: Tag the Mercenary guard farthest from Tarn.  He will come with only one friend.  The two of them are easy for your group to handle, especially since you can mez one easily.
<br />

<br />
Step 2: Approach the remaining Mercenary guard until he agros on you from proximity alone -- do not tag anything with a spell or attack.  The remaining merc and Tarn will come by themselves, leaving the 3 excavators.
<br />

<br />
Note: There is an excellent chance you will get a Phase Spider add during this pull.  Even though the 3 excavators don't chain agro with Tarn, the Phase Spider behind his building usually does.  Just remember, you CAN charm Phase Spiders and you can mez the Merc.  This will make Tarn an easy one-group kill.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
Code of Silence<br>
Luclin Server</span></td>
