				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmm. I did this about 4 days ago.. I had no problems. Did it with me (70 bard), 70 cleric healing, and a 70 ranger tanking. owned all the guards and tarn. fade pulled em single with zero problems with their pathing. pulled the one closest and none of the others aggrod if i remembered correctly. killed him. Them pulled the one closest to the edge (farthest from macklin) and both came. let them get semi close then faded. They pathed back in such a way that i could tag the straggler with a slow song and he came single. methodically killed both mobs. The gaurds next to macklin were lullable and i pull macklin single and we owned him. He is gimp as his guards are but just has slightly more health. Ranger had no problems tanking any of them. The pull/fade method worked fine for me.
<br />

<br />
Also as a side note.. I got all the bones also. I ran to every single bone pile and never saw a single ground spawn of any kind for the bones. I had to melee constructs for hours to get all the bones. I solo'd for all the bones and it was easy. Dunno if the ground spawn thing was nerfed or what. Just wanted the bards to know u can solo the constructs they are gimpage.
<br />

